shared_text:
Freddie Harrison is with Kelly Lynn Hawkins and 31 others.
September 1 at 10:37 AM ¬∑

I pray this communication finds all of you safe. As we work through the devastation of Lake Charles and surrounding areas caused by Hurricane Laura. We at lake Charles College Prep ask our students, parents, and employees to please be patient as we work toward developing the best plan possible to help address our students academic and socio-emotional needs.

Hurricane Laura has caused some significant damage to the infrastructure of the city, including electricity and water outages. There has also been roof and water damage to LCCP school building.

Due to these circumstances, Lake Charles College Prep will be closed (for both hybrid and virtual students) until the basic necessities are up and running for the city and we are able to get a true clean up underway at the school. Once this happens, we will update you on next steps, including the possibility of moving to our ‚Äúphase 1‚Äù plan while we get the school back in working condition.‚Äù
